
This starts the backend on port 8000 and the frontend on port 5173.  
The frontend is configured to talk to the backend via the Docker internal network.

## Important Notes

- The backend includes CORS middleware configured to allow all origins during development.
- The frontend's API client sends requests to `http://localhost:8000` when running locally (no Docker), or to `http://backend:8000` when running inside Docker.
- Health check endpoint: `GET /health` returns `{"status": "ok"}`.
